Answer.TalkMore: Did you like any of the old episodes? I'm sure you have a favorite one that somehow captured your fancy. Do you like it better than any of the modern episodes, or do you think no matter how good an old episode was, it can't compare with even the worst of the new episodes?
Answer.negative: I don't know about that. Everyone today just wants explosions and sex in their television shows. The old Dr. Who was about the story, not the boobs. I hate shows that are all about sex.
Answer.positive: I agree; the way they filmed those old ones made them look like soap operas and the writing of early science fiction was so formulaic that after you'd seen one episode, you'd seen them all. It makes the new versions look so much better.
Answer.rhetorical: The show finally started attracting mainstream writers. I wonder when the 'purely science fiction' writers went away and the 'real' writers took over?
